    <text id="B0700T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>Waldo inquires as to why Mines seized a horse from the couple to whom he had sold
                    it.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">RF and AL</abbr> 4
                    <abbr expan="Division">Div</abbr> 9 <abbr expan="Sub-District">Sub
                        Dist</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient"><abbr expan="John">Jno</abbr> Mines<lb/>Newport - Augusta
                            <abbr expan="County">Co</abbr>
                        <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1868-11-04"><abbr expan="November">Nov.</abbr> 4, 1868</date>
                        <name type="place">Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir -</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>You will please file your statement in this office without delay, setting forth
                    by what authority you claim &amp; have taken possession of one horse
                    property of Lucy &amp; <abbr expan="John">Jno</abbr> Wells (colored) of
                    Moffits Creek - which horse was purchased of you by them &amp; paid for with
                    30 bushels of oats &amp; one cow property of said Lucy &amp; <abbr
                        expan="John">Jno.</abbr> Wells.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very respectfully &amp;c</salute>
                    <signed>Roswell Waldo<lb/><abbr expan="Assistant Sub Assistant Commissioner"
                            >A.S.A. Comr</abbr></signed>
                    <seg type="postscript">Mr. Mines reported personally <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> and stated
                        that the horse had been <del rend="none" hand="h1"/> to Lucy Wells and he
                            <unclear>relieved</unclear><unclear>of</unclear><del hand="h1"
                            /><unclear>-----bility</unclear><del rend="none" hand="h1"/></seg>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
